sentences.en: Emerging as the times require, the approach of computerization has its unexampled advantage over others.
sentences.cn: 数字化表达方式是顺应时代的发展应运而生的, 自然有其它方式无可比拟的优越性.

sentences.en: Hong Band is an important part of Ningbo Band. The plentiful achievements they have made in academic research are unexampled by other groups in Ningbo Band.
sentences.cn: 红帮是“宁波帮”的一个重要组成部分，他们在学术研究方面的丰硕成果，是其他“宁波帮”群体无可比拟的。

sentences.en: I can no longer help thanking you for your unexampled kindness to my poor sister.
sentences.cn: 你对我那位可怜的妹妹情义太重,我再也不能不感激你了.

sentences.en: Our comradeship and our brotherhood in war were unexampled.
sentences.cn: 我们在战争年代同舟共济的兄弟情谊是史无前例的.

sentences.en: The technology has unexampled predominance comparing with other packaging technologies about aspect of high reliability and high density.
sentences.cn: 它在高可靠性、高密度方面具有其它组装技术无可比拟的优势。

sentences.en: We ask for an unexampled effort, believing that it can be made by them.
sentences.cn: 我们要求他们作出前所未有的努力, 我们相信他们是可以办到的.

sentences.en: Witchcraft blazed forth with unexampled virulence ( Montague Summers )
sentences.cn: 巫术以无先例的毒性蔓延( 蒙塔古萨默斯 )

trans.tran_cn: <正>绝无仅有的，无先例的，空前的
